      "is_bot": false,
      "login": "glwagner",
      "name": "Gregory L. Wagner"
    },
    "body": "This PR adds an AGENTS.md file that helps guide AI tools in writing decent code. This file is an excellent target for community collaboration, because AI tools produce pretty bad code unless you really them very explicitly what to do. Having a detailed AGENTS.md file is one way to do that.\r\n\r\nThis is really a draft and I would love feedback on this. The way I have been working, when I ask for a task and I notice that an agent did a bad job or made a categorical mistake (eg using `model` inside a kernel, failing to use `xnode` or `ynode`, etc), then I add an admonition to the AGENTS.md file. I hope with enough accumulation of experience, all of us will develop more efficiently.\r\n\r\nFor more information about AGENTS.md check this out: https://agents.md/",
